            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> kind congratulations &amp; y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Letters of Jan. 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> &amp; 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> oblige me much I sent the account of the Tomb
                    &amp; the drawing to that curious work <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0222">the
                            antiquaryâ€™s Repertory</title></bibl> to be published &amp; the drawing
                    to be engraven.</p>
                <p>Pray present my thanks to the Gentleman who communicated it. I have not <unclear reason="illegible">Ware</unclear> so hazard the inscription.</p>
                <p>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> account of the subject of my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0020">Br. Zool.</title></bibl> will be most welcome
                    as will the sequel to the Catalogue. remember <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0141">Ballendine</title></bibl>.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline>Febr. 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1777.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
